import Mathlib

/-- Open mapping theorem for holomorphic functions: if U âŠ‚ â„‚ is open and f : â„‚ â†’ â„‚ is
analytic on U and nonconstant on U (there exist two points in U with different images),
then the restriction of f to U is an open map. -/
theorem open_mapping_theorem_complex {U : Set â„‚} (hU : IsOpen U) {f : â„‚ â†’ â„‚}
    (hf : AnalyticOn â„‚ f U) (hnonconst : âˆƒ z1 z2, z1 âˆˆ U âˆ§ z2 âˆˆ U âˆ§ f z1 â‰  f z2) :
    IsOpenMap (fun z : Subtype U => f z) := by sorry
